oney nrdt-r.\nIf aent otherwine we will not be reiponMble for\nniim-iirfi(e, A'blrem TH CHikWAiM Pi HI.IiH\ntN'i I'o., Vinlta, I. T.\n?Ieeiineii copiei nent free on app!i':'ition\nWednesday, Vixita, Okla. Oct.. :0\nThere are a wliole lot of Hi in\nHam financiers who envy that\nNew Jersev man who has been\nasleep six weeks.\nWell, it's all settled and the\ndiscussion may be called off. The\nMohonk conference has decided\nthat we must keep the Philip\npines.\nCarry Nation now announces\nherself to be \"an airent in the\nhands of Providence.\" Hereto\nfore she has been in the hands of\nthe police, mostly.\nAjax got a conspicuous place\nin heathen mythology by defying\nthe lightning, but what Foraker\nis to get by defying Roosevelt is\nstill in the lap of the future.\nEvidently Mr. Pryan thinks\nthe tariff revision postponers are\nequally as bad as the standpat\nters, and that Taft is the biggest\n\"postponer\" of them all.\nIt frequently happens that\npunishment for the guilty hurts\nthe innocent, but no upright\njudge would accept that as a\nreason for not punishing the\nguilty.\nWhatever may have been his\npersonal wishes, the 107,000 ma\njority for the Oklahoma consti\ntution convinced the President\nthat official obstacles to statehood\ncould not be justified.\nA financial panic, big or little,\nis always a bad thing; but it is\nfar better to take the risk of one\nthan to allow abunch of unscrup\nulous high financiers to cause the\nrest of the world to regard all\nAmericans as thieves.\nBallooning may be great sport\nbut it will be some time before\nthe most of us keep one tied iu\nthe back yard for private use,\neven if Chicago wives are order\ning them for Christmas gifts lor\ntheir hubbies.\nIn Vde Earnharts Great Success\n\"Enne Fern me flisteriense\nA W0A1AN OF MYSTERY.\nA Beautiful Play\nA Beautiful Story\nHandsomely Mounted\nGeorgeously Costumed.\ni\nPRICES: 25. 50 AND 75 CENTS. BOXES $1.00\nSEATS OS SALE AT POSTOFFICE BOOK STORE.\n1\nChecking Accounts\nYou i check book will give you constantly at hand\nthe means of paying your bills without the possi\nbilities of error in mating change and the cancelled\nchecks returned to you by the bank each month\ngives you positive a\"nd indisputable receipts for all\nbills you pay, It is getting to be quite the thing for\nhousewives to carry separate or household expense\naccounts at the bank. TRY ONE.\nInternational Bank and Trust Company\nof which yesterday held a meet\ning for the purpose of consider\ning the outlook and considering\nwhat precautionary methods to\npursue. A report ci mis meet\ning was published in the Daily\nChieftain yesterday afternoon\nand shows that the banking in-\ntitutions of Vinita have avail\nable funds aggregating $370,000,\nwhich is ample to meet the de\nmands of customers and deposit\nors. 1 tie report or me conierence\nfollows\n\"Representatives of the First\nNational bank, Vinita National\nbank, Farmers' National, Chero\nkee National and the Inter\nnational Bank Trust Co., of\nVinita, met at o'clock Tuesday\nafternoon, and after carefully\nconsulting together in regard to\nthe financial situation, found\nthemselves in good condition,\nand able to take eare of the situ\nation in this locality. i\n'We have on hand cash and\nsight exchange :J76,000, which\nis ample.\n'We agree to stand together\nto protect the business of the\ncommunity without interruption,\nand will be found with our doors\nopen every day, transacting\nbusiness as usual.\nThe banks of Vinita are rated\namong the soundest in the new\nstate, and it is pleasing to know\nthat under prevailing conditions\nthey have today their vaults full\nof money and are able to meet\nanv and all legitimate demands.\nWhile many other banks are\ntaking a six days' special holiday\nfor their own protection, the\nauks of Vinita are keeping open\nlouse and transacting ousiness\nin the usual way.\nWinter's\nOil a tn i t i re f\ns-HSi ruining i\nYou know what that\nmeans to you.\nWhy not plan now\nwhere to